The paper deals with deep learning algorithms for connectomics, which involves analyzing and segmenting 3D images of neurons. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses unsupervised training and the use of convolutional neural networks, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the creation of a dataset, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for labeling and organizing the data.
